00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:54.000
BUT HE'S THE ONLY PARENT
I HAVE RIGHT NOW.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:57.000
SO I NEED
TO HELP HIM OUT

00:04:57.000 --> 00:04:59.000
A LOT MORE
THAN NORMAL.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:04.000
Brazelton:
 IT HASN'T BEEN EASY
 FOR MARTY OR THE KIDS,

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:09.000
BUT MARTY'S HAD
 THE SUPPORT OF HIS FAITH
 AND HIS FAMILY

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:13.000
AND THE STRONG ROLE MODEL
 OF HIS OWN FATHER,

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:16.000
A BAPTIST PASTOR.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:19.000
Marty:
 MY DAD HAS TAUGHT ME
 A LOT OF THINGS:

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:22.000
RESPECT, DISCIPLINE.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:25.000
AND NOW THOSE THINGS ARE
HELPING ME TO RAISE MY KIDS.

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:27.000
Marty:
 GIVE PAPA A KISS
 AND LET'S GO BYE-BYE.

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:30.000
Gradis Eggleston Jr:
 MARTY CAME FROM A HOME

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:34.000
WHERE LOVE WAS 
FIRST PRIORITY.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:38.000
AND HE COULD NOT
LEAVE THAT STRUCTURE

00:05:38.000 --> 00:05:41.000
AND TAKE
ANY OTHER AVENUE

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:43.000
BUT THE ONE THAT HAD BEEN
INSTILLED WITHIN HIM.

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:46.000
Brazelton:
 MARTY SHARED HIS LESSONS
 WITH OTHERS.

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:50.000
HE RUNS
 "FATHERS' INITIATIVE,"
 A SOURCE OF SUPPORT

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:51.000
FOR DADS IN THE COMMUNITY.

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:53.000
Marty:
 I CAME HERE...

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:55.000
WE'RE GONNA GO
SEE THE BABIES.

00:05:55.000 --> 00:05:58.000
...JUST TO KINDA
 ADD TO MY OWN SKILLS

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:00.000
AND LEARN SOME
 FATHERING TECHNIQUES

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:02.000
AND I FELL IN LOVE
 WITH IT.

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:04.000
YOU DON'T WANNA GET
CHANNELED INTO THAT

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:06.000
POLICEMAN ROLE
WITH YOUR KIDS.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:08.000
AND SO IT'S OUR JOB
NOT TO BULLY THEM,

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:11.000
AND NOT TO SAY,
"HEY, YOU CAN'T DO THAT.
YOU CAN'T DO THAT,"

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:13.000
- BUT TO GUIDE THEM.
- A LOT OF PEOPLE THINK

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:17.000
THAT AS FATHERS, AS MEN,
WE DON'T WANNA BE BOTHERED
WITH THEM.

00:06:17.000 --> 00:06:19.000
- RIGHT.
- AND THEY'RE WRONG.

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:21.000
IT'S NATURAL
TO BE ABLE TO CARE.

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:24.000
I MEAN, WE HAVE THOSE
INSTINCTS THAT ARE BUILT
WITHIN JUST LIKE MOMS DO.

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
BUT WE HAVE TO STEP UP
AND MAKE SURE WE TAKE
OUR POSITION

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
IN THE LIVES OF OUR CHILDREN
AND NOT TAKE THAT BACK SEAT.

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:34.000
SO WHAT WE NEED TO DO
IS UNDERSTAND

00:06:34.000 --> 00:06:36.000
THAT WE HAVE TO
BE THERE FOR THEM.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:38.000
YOU KNOW, SOMETHING THAT YOU
TELL YOUR SON RIGHT NOW

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:42.000
OR TELL YOUR DAUGHTER
RIGHT NOW WILL LAST LONGER
THAN ANYTHING ELSE.

00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:45.000
WHOA, LET DADDY
HELP YOU, OKAY, MISS LADY?

